<doc id="1129803" wikidata="Q5437706" url="?curid=1129803" title="Fatherland Front">
<text>Fatherland Front may refer to:

* Fatherland Front (Austria), the ruling political organisation of Austrofascism, 1933–1938
* Fatherland Front (Bulgaria), a communist resistance movement during World War II, dissolved in 1990
* National Fatherland Front, an umbrella organization for the People&#x27;s Democratic Party of Afghanistan
* United Democratic Fatherland Front, a North Korean united front led by the Workers&#x27; Party of Korea
* Vietnamese Fatherland Front, a pro-government umbrella group</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q695482" start="34" end="60" title="Fatherland Front (Austria)" label="Fatherland Front (Austria)"/>
<link wikidata="Q2453048" start="126" end="153" title="Fatherland Front (Bulgaria)" label="Fatherland Front (Bulgaria)"/>
